# /etc/cron.d/fxmily-app — Fxmily V1 production cron schedule (J10).
#
# Owner   : root (system crond reads /etc/cron.d/* with mode 0644).
# User    : fxmily (each row's 6th field — non-privileged execution).
# Wrapper : /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron sources /etc/fxmily/cron.env
#           which is mode 0600 owner fxmily, so the secret never appears
#           in `ps -ef` / `journalctl` / this file.
#
# Schedule philosophy : every cron is anchored to an off-hours slot for
# `Europe/Paris` (V1 single-TZ cohort) and spaced so two long-running
# jobs never overlap on the CX22 (2 vCPU, 4 GB RAM).
#
# ⚠ TIMEZONE REALITY (tour 13) : the host runs `Europe/Paris`
# (/etc/localtime, set at provisioning 2026-05-02) and Debian crond
# interprets /etc/cron.d hour fields in the HOST-LOCAL timezone, NOT
# UTC (no CRON_TZ support in Debian vixie-cron). Proven at runtime:
# checkin-reminders logged ticks 17:00→18:45 UTC = 19:00→20:45 Paris
# for an `18-20` hour field (cron.log 2026-07-04). Historical comments
# below that say "UTC" describe the local wall-clock hour — for the
# off-hours jobs the 1-2 h offset is harmless, and local-time
# scheduling is actually what the Paris member windows want (DST-proof).
#
# Wired routes (POST + X-Cron-Secret SHA-256 verify timingSafeEqual) :
#
#   - checkin-reminders         every 15 min, 07-09 + 20-22 Paris (member windows, J5)
#   - recompute-scores          daily 02:00 UTC                    (J6)
#   - dispatch-douglas          every 6 h                          (J7)
#   - weekly-reports            Sunday 21:00 UTC                   (J8)
#   - dispatch-notifications    every 2 min                        (J9)
#   - purge-deleted             daily 03:00 UTC                    (J10)
#   - purge-push-subscriptions  Sunday 05:00 UTC                   (J10)
#   - purge-audit-log           daily 04:00 UTC                    (J10)
#   - fxmily-caddy-backup       Sunday 06:30 UTC                   (V1.12)
#   - fxmily-uploads-backup     daily 06:45 UTC                    (A-Z DR)
#   - mindset-check-reminders   Monday 09:00 UTC                   (V1.5 §27)
#   - generate-meetings         weekdays 06:00 UTC                 (V1.7 §30)
#   - purge-access-requests     Sunday 04:00 UTC                   (V2.5 RGPD)
#   - calendar-overdue-alert    daily 11:00 UTC                    (S5 §26 perm.)
#   - monthly-debrief-overdue-alert daily 11:10 UTC                (S5 §25 perm.)
#   - onboarding-profile-overdue-alert daily 11:20 UTC             (S2 perm.)
#   - verification-scan         daily 11:30 UTC                    (S3 §33.5)
#   - weekly-report-overdue-alert daily 11:40 UTC                  (J8 perm.)
#   - verification-batch-overdue-alert daily 11:50 UTC            (AUTONOMY-1 perm.)
#   - admin-daily-brief         daily 07:05 Paris                  (Tour 15 brief)
#
# Log : every run appends one line to /var/log/fxmily/cron.log via the
# wrapper. The DB audit row (`cron.<route>.scan`) is the canonical
# record (counts + threshold + ranAt) — this log is just for ops triage.

SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
MAILTO=""

# m h dom mon dow user command

# J5 — check-in reminders : every 15 min, anchored to the Paris-LOCAL due windows
# 07:30→09:00 + 20:30→22:00 (lib/checkin/timezone.ts). Since crond reads these
# hours in HOST-LOCAL Europe/Paris time (see header), local hours 7-9 + 20-22 are
# an exact DST-proof SUPERSET of the member windows: the in-window guard +
# DB dedup make the out-of-window ticks (07:00-07:15, 09:15-09:45, 20:00-20:15,
# 22:15-22:45) harmless no-ops.
# TOUR 13 FIX: the previous `5-7,18-20` field was designed as UTC (S10 dual-DST
# superset) but crond read it as Paris-local → ticks fired 05:00-07:45 + 18:00-20:45
# Paris, covering only the FIRST 15-30 min of each member window (07:30/07:45 +
# 20:30/20:45). Members due later in the window were silently never nudged, since
# provisioning (May). Exposed by the tour-12 windowed health model (first honest
# red 2026-07-04 19:37Z). Guarded by reminder-cron-window.test.ts.
0,15,30,45 7-9,20-22 * * *   fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron checkin-reminders

# J6 — behavioral score recompute : nightly 02:00 UTC.
0 2 * * *                    fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron recompute-scores

# J7 — Mark Douglas temporal dispatch : every 6 hours.
0 0,6,12,18 * * *            fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron dispatch-douglas

# J8 — Weekly AI report (admin digest) : Sunday 21:00 UTC.
0 21 * * 0                   fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron weekly-reports

# J9 — Web Push dispatcher : every 2 minutes.
*/2 * * * *                  fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron dispatch-notifications

# J10 — RGPD soft-delete materialise + 30d hard-purge : daily 03:00 UTC.
0 3 * * *                    fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron purge-deleted

# J10 — Stale push subscriptions cleanup (90d) : Sunday 05:00 UTC.
0 5 * * 0                    fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron purge-push-subscriptions

# J10 — Audit log retention purge (90d) : daily 04:00 UTC (1h after purge-deleted).
0 4 * * *                    fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron purge-audit-log

# J10 — Postgres backup (pg_dump → GPG → R2) : daily 02:30 UTC.
30 2 * * *                   fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-backup

# V1.12 — Caddy data volume backup (Let's Encrypt certs preservation) :
# Sunday 06:30 UTC. Weekly cadence is sufficient — Let's Encrypt renews
# ~60 days, Caddy auto-renews at ~30 days remaining. Off-hours
# Europe/Paris, no overlap with the daily 03:00/04:00 purge slots or
# the 06:00 dispatch-douglas slot.
30 6 * * 0                   fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-caddy-backup

# A-Z DR — member uploads volume backup (irreplaceable proof evidence) :
# DAILY 06:45 UTC. The `fxmily-uploads` volume is the ONLY copy of MT5
# proofs / trade screenshots / training shots; the DB stores only the keys
# (Mt5AccountProof.fileKey / Trade.screenshotEntryKey / TradeMedia.fileKey).
# Without this, a disk/host loss leaves every restored key 404-ing forever
# (the §33 anti-lie evidence gone). DAILY (vs the weekly cert backup)
# because uploads are member-generated + irreplaceable. Off-hours
# Europe/Paris; offsets the Sunday 06:30 caddy backup and the 06:00
# dispatch-douglas / generate-meetings slots. Hard-fails (exit 4) when
# BACKUP_REQUIRE_OFFSITE=1 and R2 is unconfigured (§9-B durability).
45 6 * * *                   fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-uploads-backup

# Tour 14 §9-B — monthly PROVEN-RESTORE drill : 1st Sunday 05:00 Paris. A
# backup you have never restored is a hope, not a backup. This runs EVERY
# Sunday 05:00 but the script self-gates to the 1st Sunday only (Debian crond
# ORs a restricted dom+dow, so the "1st Sunday" logic lives in the binary, not
# this field). It takes the freshest encrypted pg dump, restores it into a
# DISPOSABLE, network-isolated (`--network none`, no published port) scratch
# Postgres, and asserts real tables + rows exist (users/daily_checkins/trades).
# NEVER touches prod. 05:10 is clear of the 02:30 pg backup, the 06:30/06:45
# volume backups AND the 05:00 purge-push-subscriptions (CX22 = 2 vCPU — the
# scratch-postgres restore should not race another job). Logs the verdict to
# cron.log; pings HEALTHCHECK_PING_URL_RESTORE on success if set.
# Tour 15 — fired through the fxmily-cron wrapper (LOCAL task, not an HTTP
# route): the root validator on the host never self-updates, so crontab lines
# must only ever use shapes its OLDEST deployed generation accepts. The
# tour-14 direct `fxmily-restore-drill` line failed the 2026-07-06 deploy
# against the tour-12 validator still installed on the host.
10 5 * * 0                   fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron restore-drill

# V1.5 §27 — QCM athlète weekly mindset reminder : Monday 09:00 UTC. The
# mindset week opens Monday (`weekStart`); one gentle anti-FOMO nudge per
# week (no email). 09:00 UTC is a free Monday slot — no overlap with the
# 07:00-08:00 check-in windows nor the daily 02:00-05:00 / 0,6,12,18
# off-hours jobs. Idempotent (scan skips already-submitted / already-nudged).
0 9 * * 1                    fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron mindset-check-reminders

# V1.7 §30 — Fxmily meeting slot generation : weekdays 06:00 UTC. Materialises
# the rolling [today, today+7] window of Mon–Fri 12h/20h Paris slots (DST-aware,
# weekends auto-skipped by the occurrence generator). A generous lead before the
# day's earliest 12h Paris slot (10:00/11:00 UTC). Idempotent on @@unique(date,
# slot) → a missed weekday run self-heals on the next (re-run = 0 duplicate).
# Shares the 06:00 slot with dispatch-douglas (0 0,6,12,18) — both are short
# (a createMany / a temporal scan), no contention on the CX22.
0 6 * * 1-5                  fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron generate-meetings

# V2.5 — Self-service access requests RGPD purge : Sunday 04:00 UTC. Deletes
# rejected rows + pending/approved rows older than 30 days so the table never
# accumulates dormant non-member PII (name+email without account consent). The
# 04:00 Sunday slot shares the hour with the daily purge-audit-log (04:00) but
# they hit disjoint tables; both are short deleteMany scans, no CX22 contention.
0 4 * * 0                    fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron purge-access-requests

# Session 5 §26 — calendar overdue admin nudge : daily 11:00 UTC (13:00 Paris).
# DETECTION-ONLY safety-net for the MANUAL calendar batch (ban-risk human-in-the-
# loop §5.4 — the generation is NEVER cronned). Scans the current Paris week for
# members with a filled questionnaire but no generated calendar past the grace
# window, and emails the admin so nothing slips silently (DoD#4 permanence). Pure
# read + idempotent ; emits cron.calendar_overdue.scan heartbeat (monitored by
# lib/system/health.ts). 11:00 UTC is a free midday slot — no overlap with the
# 02:00-06:00 nightly jobs nor the 07:00-08:00 check-in windows.
0 11 * * *                   fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron calendar-overdue-alert

# Session 5 §25 — monthly debrief overdue admin nudge : daily 11:10 UTC (13:10 Paris).
# DETECTION-ONLY safety-net for the MANUAL monthly debrief batch (ban-risk human-
# in-the-loop §5.4 — the generation is NEVER cronned). Scans the last completed
# civil month for active members with no debrief past the grace window, and emails
# the admin so no member silently loses their monthly debrief (DoD#2, SPEC §25.4).
# Pure read + idempotent ; emits cron.monthly_debrief_overdue.scan heartbeat
# (monitored by lib/system/health.ts). 11:10 UTC offsets the 11:00 calendar nudge.
10 11 * * *                  fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron monthly-debrief-overdue-alert

# S2 — onboarding profile overdue admin nudge : daily 11:20 UTC (13:20 Paris).
# DETECTION-ONLY safety-net for the MANUAL onboarding profiling batch (ban-risk
# human-in-the-loop §5.4 — the generation is NEVER cronned). Scans for completed
# onboarding interviews of active members with no MemberProfile past the 24h
# grace (the member-facing « dans les prochaines 24h » promise), and emails the
# admin so no member silently waits forever for their profile. Pure read +
# idempotent ; emits cron.onboarding_profile_overdue.scan heartbeat (monitored
# by lib/system/health.ts). 11:20 UTC offsets the 11:00/11:10 permanence nudges.
20 11 * * *                  fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron onboarding-profile-overdue-alert

# S3 §33.5 — daily verification scan : 11:30 UTC (13:30 Paris). DETERMINISTIC
# fold of rows already produced (reconcile declared↔extracted, ritual events,
# weekly ConstancyScore, repetition-only alerts + Mark Douglas dispatch). It
# NEVER drives Claude — the vision batch stays manual (ban-risk human-in-the-
# loop §5.4). Idempotent (deterministic event ids + identity-deduped écarts) ;
# emits cron.verification_scan.scan heartbeat (monitored by
# lib/system/health.ts). 11:30 UTC offsets the 11:00/11:10/11:20 nudges.
30 11 * * *                  fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron verification-scan

# J8 — weekly report overdue admin nudge : daily 11:40 UTC (13:40 Paris).
# DETECTION-ONLY safety-net for the MANUAL weekly digest batch (ban-risk human-
# in-the-loop §5.4 — ops/scripts/weekly-batch-local.sh, the generation is NEVER
# cronned in the local-batch operating mode). Scans the last completed full
# Mon→Sun week for active members with no WeeklyReport row past the grace window,
# and emails the admin so the weekly digest never silently goes ungenerated
# (SPEC §7.10). Pure read + idempotent ; emits cron.weekly_report_overdue.scan
# heartbeat (monitored by lib/system/health.ts). 11:40 UTC offsets the
# 11:00/11:10/11:20 permanence nudges and the 11:30 verification scan.
40 11 * * *                  fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron weekly-report-overdue-alert

# AUTONOMY-1 — MT5 proof vision overdue admin nudge : daily 11:50 UTC (13:50 Paris).
# DETECTION-ONLY safety-net for the MANUAL MT5 vision batch (ban-risk human-in-the-
# loop §5.4 — ops/scripts/verification-batch-local.sh, the analysis is NEVER cronned).
# 5th twin of the calendar/monthly/onboarding/weekly nets : the vision batch was the
# only local Claude pipeline without an anti-oubli nudge. Scans for MT5 proofs of
# active members still `pending` past the 24h grace, and emails the admin so no
# member silently waits forever for their account/positions to be extracted. Pure
# read + idempotent ; emits cron.verification_overdue.scan heartbeat (monitored by
# lib/system/health.ts). 11:50 UTC offsets the 11:00/11:10/11:20/11:40 permanence
# nudges and the 11:30 verification scan.
50 11 * * *                  fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron verification-batch-overdue-alert

# Tour 15 — daily ADMIN brief (« point du matin ») : 07:05 Paris-LOCAL. The coach
# gets a count-only, PII-free brief of where to look today (triage counts, new
# behavioral signals since yesterday, members drifting away — all REUSED from
# already-stored signals). A STANDING report, not an alert: it emails every day
# (even a calm one) so silence means a broken cron, never a quiet day. Pure read +
# idempotent ; emits cron.admin_daily_brief.scan heartbeat (monitored by
# lib/system/health.ts). 07:05 Paris is the first workable morning slot: crond
# reads this hour as HOST-LOCAL Europe/Paris (see header), and minute :05 sits
# clear of the check-in-reminder ticks (0,15,30,45) at 07h so the two short jobs
# never race on the CX22. It NEVER drives Claude (no generation on a server).
5 7 * * *                    fxmily   /usr/local/bin/fxmily-cron admin-daily-brief

# §9-C SELF-HEALING — container autoheal watchdog : every minute, as ROOT.
# `restart: unless-stopped` (docker-compose.prod.yml) only restarts a container
# that has EXITED — never one that is running-but-UNHEALTHY (DB pool deadlock,
# event-loop stall, wedged dependency → Docker marks it `unhealthy`, Caddy 502s,
# nothing heals it). This watchdog polls the Docker HEALTHCHECK and restarts the
# `fxmily-web` container when unhealthy, with a 5-min cooldown so it can't thrash
# and a loud ESCALATION log line when a restart didn't fix it (self-heal tried,
# human needed). Runs as ROOT (not `fxmily`) because `docker restart` needs the
# Docker daemon socket; the script itself only ever touches our own containers.
# Idempotent + cheap (one `docker inspect` when healthy).
* * * * *                    root     /usr/local/bin/fxmily-autoheal
